7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // This file implements the LiveDebugVariables analysis. ----
10 // ----
11 // Remove all DBG_VALUE instructions referencing virtual registers and replace ----
12 // them with a data structure tracking where live user variables are kept - in a ----
13 // virtual register or in a stack slot. ----
14 // ----
15 // Allow the data structure to be updated during register allocation when values ----
16 // are moved between registers and stack slots. Finally emit new DBG_VALUE ----
17 // instructions after register allocation is complete. ----
18 // ----
19 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
20 ----

99 /// Describes a debug variable value by location number and expression along ----
100 /// with some flags about the original usage of the location. ----
101 class DbgVariableValue { ----
102 public: ----
103 DbgVariableValue(ArrayRef NewLocs, bool WasIndirect, bool WasList, 0
104 const DIExpression &Expr) ----
105 : WasIndirect(WasIndirect), WasList(WasList), Expression(&Expr) { 0
106 assert(!(WasIndirect && WasList) && 0
107 "DBG_VALUE_LISTs should not be indirect."); ----
108 SmallVector LocNoVec; 0
109 for (unsigned LocNo : NewLocs) { 0
110 auto It = find(LocNoVec, LocNo); 0
111 if (It == LocNoVec.end()) 0
112 LocNoVec.push_back(LocNo); 0
113 else { ----
114 // Loc duplicates an element in LocNos; replace references to Op ----
115 // with references to the duplicating element. ----
116 unsigned OpIdx = LocNoVec.size(); 0
117 unsigned DuplicatingIdx = std::distance(LocNoVec.begin(), It); 0
118 Expression = 0
119 DIExpression::replaceArg(Expression, OpIdx, DuplicatingIdx); 0
120 } ----
121 } ----
122 // FIXME: Debug values referencing 64+ unique machine locations are rare and ----
123 // currently unsupported for performance reasons. If we can verify that ----
124 // performance is acceptable for such debug values, we can increase the ----
125 // bit-width of LocNoCount to 14 to enable up to 16384 unique machine ----
126 // locations. We will also need to verify that this does not cause issues ----
127 // with LiveDebugVariables' use of IntervalMap. ----
128 if (LocNoVec.size() < 64) { 0
129 LocNoCount = LocNoVec.size(); 0
130 if (LocNoCount > 0) { 0
131 LocNos = std::make_unique(LocNoCount); 0
132 std::copy(LocNoVec.begin(), LocNoVec.end(), loc_nos_begin()); 0
133 } ----
134 } else { ----
135 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Found debug value with 64+ unique machine " 0
136 "locations, dropping...\n"); ----
137 LocNoCount = 1; 0
138 // Turn this into an undef debug value list; right now, the simplest form ----
139 // of this is an expression with one arg, and an undef debug operand. ----
140 Expression = 0
141 DIExpression::get(Expr.getContext(), {dwarf::DW_OP_LLVM_arg, 0}); 0
142 if (auto FragmentInfoOpt = Expr.getFragmentInfo()) 0
143 Expression = *DIExpression::createFragmentExpression( 0
144 Expression, FragmentInfoOpt->OffsetInBits, 0
145 FragmentInfoOpt->SizeInBits); 0
146 LocNos = std::make_unique(LocNoCount); 0
147 LocNos[0] = UndefLocNo; 0
148 } ----
149 } 0
150 ----
151 DbgVariableValue() : LocNoCount(0), WasIndirect(false), WasList(false) {} 0
152 DbgVariableValue(const DbgVariableValue &Other) 0
153 : LocNoCount(Other.LocNoCount), WasIndirect(Other.getWasIndirect()), 0
154 WasList(Other.getWasList()), Expression(Other.getExpression()) { 0
155 if (Other.getLocNoCount()) { 0
156 LocNos.reset(new unsigned[Other.getLocNoCount()]); 0
157 std::copy(Other.loc_nos_begin(), Other.loc_nos_end(), loc_nos_begin()); 0
158 } ----
159 } 0
160 ----
161 DbgVariableValue &operator=(const DbgVariableValue &Other) { 0
162 if (this == &Other) 0
163 return *this; 0
164 if (Other.getLocNoCount()) { 0
165 LocNos.reset(new unsigned[Other.getLocNoCount()]); 0
166 std::copy(Other.loc_nos_begin(), Other.loc_nos_end(), loc_nos_begin()); 0
167 } else { ----
168 LocNos.release(); 0
169 } ----
170 LocNoCount = Other.getLocNoCount(); 0
171 WasIndirect = Other.getWasIndirect(); 0
172 WasList = Other.getWasList(); 0
173 Expression = Other.getExpression(); 0
174 return *this; 0
175 } ----
176 ----
177 const DIExpression *getExpression() const { return Expression; } 0
178 uint8_t getLocNoCount() const { return LocNoCount; } 0
179 bool containsLocNo(unsigned LocNo) const { 0
180 return is_contained(loc_nos(), LocNo); 0
181 } ----
182 bool getWasIndirect() const { return WasIndirect; } 0
183 bool getWasList() const { return WasList; } 0
184 bool isUndef() const { return LocNoCount == 0 || containsLocNo(UndefLocNo); } 0
185 ----
186 DbgVariableValue decrementLocNosAfterPivot(unsigned Pivot) const { 0
187 SmallVector NewLocNos; 0
188 for (unsigned LocNo : loc_nos()) 0
189 NewLocNos.push_back(LocNo != UndefLocNo && LocNo > Pivot ? LocNo - 1 0
190 : LocNo); ----
191 return DbgVariableValue(NewLocNos, WasIndirect, WasList, *Expression); 0
192 } 0
193 ----
194 DbgVariableValue remapLocNos(ArrayRef LocNoMap) const { 0
195 SmallVector NewLocNos; 0
196 for (unsigned LocNo : loc_nos()) 0
197 // Undef values don't exist in locations (and thus not in LocNoMap ----
198 // either) so skip over them. See getLocationNo(). ----
199 NewLocNos.push_back(LocNo == UndefLocNo ? UndefLocNo : LocNoMap[LocNo]); 0
200 return DbgVariableValue(NewLocNos, WasIndirect, WasList, *Expression); 0
201 } 0
202 ----
203 DbgVariableValue changeLocNo(unsigned OldLocNo, unsigned NewLocNo) const { 0
204 SmallVector NewLocNos; 0
205 NewLocNos.assign(loc_nos_begin(), loc_nos_end()); 0
206 auto OldLocIt = find(NewLocNos, OldLocNo); 0
207 assert(OldLocIt != NewLocNos.end() && "Old location must be present."); 0
208 *OldLocIt = NewLocNo; 0
209 return DbgVariableValue(NewLocNos, WasIndirect, WasList, *Expression); 0
210 } 0
211 ----
212 bool hasLocNoGreaterThan(unsigned LocNo) const { 0
213 return any_of(loc_nos(), 0
214 [LocNo](unsigned ThisLocNo) { return ThisLocNo > LocNo; }); 0
215 } ----
216 ----
217 void printLocNos(llvm::raw_ostream &OS) const { 0
218 for (const unsigned &Loc : loc_nos()) 0
219 OS << (&Loc == loc_nos_begin() ? " " : ", ") << Loc; 0
220 } 0
221 ----
222 friend inline bool operator==(const DbgVariableValue &LHS, 0
223 const DbgVariableValue &RHS) { ----
224 if (std::tie(LHS.LocNoCount, LHS.WasIndirect, LHS.WasList, 0
225 LHS.Expression) != 0
226 std::tie(RHS.LocNoCount, RHS.WasIndirect, RHS.WasList, RHS.Expression)) 0
227 return false; 0
228 return std::equal(LHS.loc_nos_begin(), LHS.loc_nos_end(), 0
229 RHS.loc_nos_begin()); 0
230 } ----
231 ----
232 friend inline bool operator!=(const DbgVariableValue &LHS, 0
233 const DbgVariableValue &RHS) { ----
234 return !(LHS == RHS); 0
235 } ----
236 ----
237 unsigned *loc_nos_begin() { return LocNos.get(); } 0
238 const unsigned *loc_nos_begin() const { return LocNos.get(); } 0
239 unsigned *loc_nos_end() { return LocNos.get() + LocNoCount; } ----
240 const unsigned *loc_nos_end() const { return LocNos.get() + LocNoCount; } 0
241 ArrayRef loc_nos() const { 0
242 return ArrayRef(LocNos.get(), LocNoCount); 0
243 } ----

245 private: ----
246 // IntervalMap requires the value object to be very small, to the extent ----
247 // that we do not have enough room for an std::vector. Using a C-style array ----
248 // (with a unique_ptr wrapper for convenience) allows us to optimize for this ----
249 // specific case by packing the array size into only 6 bits (it is highly ----
250 // unlikely that any debug value will need 64+ locations). ----
251 std::unique_ptr LocNos; ----
252 uint8_t LocNoCount : 6; ----
253 bool WasIndirect : 1; ----
254 bool WasList : 1; ----
255 const DIExpression *Expression = nullptr; ----
256 }; ----

278 /// A user value is a part of a debug info user variable. ----
279 /// ----
280 /// A DBG_VALUE instruction notes that (a sub-register of) a virtual register ----
281 /// holds part of a user variable. The part is identified by a byte offset. ----
282 /// ----
283 /// UserValues are grouped into equivalence classes for easier searching. Two ----
284 /// user values are related if they are held by the same virtual register. The ----
285 /// equivalence class is the transitive closure of that relation. ----
286 class UserValue { ----
287 const DILocalVariable *Variable; ///< The debug info variable we are part of. ----
288 /// The part of the variable we describe. ----
289 const std::optional Fragment; ----
290 DebugLoc dl; ///< The debug location for the variable. This is ----
291 ///< used by dwarf writer to find lexical scope. ----
292 UserValue *leader; ///< Equivalence class leader. ----
293 UserValue *next = nullptr; ///< Next value in equivalence class, or null. ----
294 ----
295 /// Numbered locations referenced by locmap. ----
296 SmallVector locations; ----
297 ----
298 /// Map of slot indices where this value is live. ----
299 LocMap locInts; ----
300 ----
301 /// Set of interval start indexes that have been trimmed to the ----
302 /// lexical scope. ----
303 SmallSet trimmedDefs; ----
304 ----
305 /// Insert a DBG_VALUE into MBB at Idx for DbgValue. ----
306 void insertDebugValue(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, SlotIndex StartIdx, ----
307 SlotIndex StopIdx, DbgVariableValue DbgValue, ----
308 ArrayRef LocSpills, ----
309 ArrayRef SpillOffsets, LiveIntervals &LIS, ----
310 const TargetInstrInfo &TII, ----
311 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, ----
312 BlockSkipInstsMap &BBSkipInstsMap); ----
313 ----
314 /// Replace OldLocNo ranges with NewRegs ranges where NewRegs ----
315 /// is live. Returns true if any changes were made. ----
316 bool splitLocation(unsigned OldLocNo, ArrayRef NewRegs, ----
317 LiveIntervals &LIS); ----
318 ----
319 public: ----
320 /// Create a new UserValue. ----
321 UserValue(const DILocalVariable *var, 0
322 std::optional Fragment, DebugLoc L, ----
323 LocMap::Allocator &alloc) ----
324 : Variable(var), Fragment(Fragment), dl(std::move(L)), leader(this), 0
325 locInts(alloc) {} 0
326 ----
327 /// Get the leader of this value's equivalence class. ----
328 UserValue *getLeader() { 0
329 UserValue *l = leader; 0
330 while (l != l->leader) 0
331 l = l->leader; 0
332 return leader = l; 0
333 } ----
334 ----
335 /// Return the next UserValue in the equivalence class. ----
336 UserValue *getNext() const { return next; } 0
337 ----
338 /// Merge equivalence classes. ----
339 static UserValue *merge(UserValue *L1, UserValue *L2) { 0
340 L2 = L2->getLeader(); 0
341 if (!L1) 0
342 return L2; 0
343 L1 = L1->getLeader(); 0
344 if (L1 == L2) 0
345 return L1; 0
346 // Splice L2 before L1's members. ----
347 UserValue *End = L2; 0
348 while (End->next) { 0
349 End->leader = L1; 0
350 End = End->next; 0
351 } ----
352 End->leader = L1; 0
353 End->next = L1->next; 0
354 L1->next = L2; 0
355 return L1; 0
356 } ----
357 ----
358 /// Return the location number that matches Loc. ----
359 /// ----
360 /// For undef values we always return location number UndefLocNo without ----
361 /// inserting anything in locations. Since locations is a vector and the ----
362 /// location number is the position in the vector and UndefLocNo is ~0, ----
363 /// we would need a very big vector to put the value at the right position. ----
364 unsigned getLocationNo(const MachineOperand &LocMO) { 0
365 if (LocMO.isReg()) { 0
366 if (LocMO.getReg() == 0) 0
367 return UndefLocNo; 0
368 // For register locations we dont care about use/def and other flags. ----
369 for (unsigned i = 0, e = locations.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
370 if (locations[i].isReg() && 0
371 locations[i].getReg() == LocMO.getReg() && 0
372 locations[i].getSubReg() == LocMO.getSubReg()) 0
373 return i; 0
374 } else ----
375 for (unsigned i = 0, e = locations.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
376 if (LocMO.isIdenticalTo(locations[i])) 0
377 return i; 0
378 locations.push_back(LocMO); 0
379 // We are storing a MachineOperand outside a MachineInstr. ----
380 locations.back().clearParent(); 0
381 // Don't store def operands. ----
382 if (locations.back().isReg()) { 0
383 if (locations.back().isDef()) 0
384 locations.back().setIsDead(false); 0
385 locations.back().setIsUse(); 0
386 } ----
387 return locations.size() - 1; 0
388 } ----
389 ----
390 /// Remove (recycle) a location number. If \p LocNo still is used by the ----
391 /// locInts nothing is done. ----
392 void removeLocationIfUnused(unsigned LocNo) { 0
393 // Bail out if LocNo still is used. ----
394 for (LocMap::const_iterator I = locInts.begin(); I.valid(); ++I) { 0
395 const DbgVariableValue &DbgValue = I.value(); 0
396 if (DbgValue.containsLocNo(LocNo)) 0
397 return; 0
398 } 0
399 // Remove the entry in the locations vector, and adjust all references to ----
400 // location numbers above the removed entry. ----
401 locations.erase(locations.begin() + LocNo); 0
402 for (LocMap::iterator I = locInts.begin(); I.valid(); ++I) { 0
403 const DbgVariableValue &DbgValue = I.value(); 0
404 if (DbgValue.hasLocNoGreaterThan(LocNo)) 0
405 I.setValueUnchecked(DbgValue.decrementLocNosAfterPivot(LocNo)); 0
406 } 0
407 } ----

409 /// Ensure that all virtual register locations are mapped. ----

412 /// Add a definition point to this user value. ----
413 void addDef(SlotIndex Idx, ArrayRef LocMOs, bool IsIndirect, 0
414 bool IsList, const DIExpression &Expr) { ----
415 SmallVector Locs; 0
416 for (const MachineOperand &Op : LocMOs) 0
417 Locs.push_back(getLocationNo(Op)); 0
418 DbgVariableValue DbgValue(Locs, IsIndirect, IsList, Expr); 0
419 // Add a singular (Idx,Idx) -> value mapping. ----
420 LocMap::iterator I = locInts.find(Idx); 0
421 if (!I.valid() || I.start() != Idx) 0
422 I.insert(Idx, Idx.getNextSlot(), std::move(DbgValue)); 0
423 else ----
424 // A later DBG_VALUE at the same SlotIndex overrides the old location. ----
425 I.setValue(std::move(DbgValue)); 0
426 } 0

442 /// \param LIS Live intervals analysis. ----

445 SmallDenseMap> ----
446 &LiveIntervalInfo, ----
447 std::optional>> &Kills, ----
448 LiveIntervals &LIS); ----

453 /// ----

457 /// \param KilledAt The point where the range of DbgValue could be extended. ----
458 /// \param [in,out] NewDefs Append (Idx, DbgValue) of inserted defs here. ----
459 void addDefsFromCopies( ----
460 DbgVariableValue DbgValue, ----
461 SmallVectorImpl> &LocIntervals, ----
462 SlotIndex KilledAt, ----
463 SmallVectorImpl> &NewDefs, ----

468 void computeIntervals(MachineRegisterInfo &MRI, const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, ----
469 LiveIntervals &LIS, LexicalScopes &LS); ----

497 /// A user label is a part of a debug info user label. ----
498 class UserLabel { ----
499 const DILabel *Label; ///< The debug info label we are part of. ----
500 DebugLoc dl; ///< The debug location for the label. This is ----
501 ///< used by dwarf writer to find lexical scope. ----
502 SlotIndex loc; ///< Slot used by the debug label. ----
503 ----
504 /// Insert a DBG_LABEL into MBB at Idx. ----
505 void insertDebugLabel(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, SlotIndex Idx, ----
506 LiveIntervals &LIS, const TargetInstrInfo &TII, ----
507 BlockSkipInstsMap &BBSkipInstsMap); ----
508 ----
509 public: ----
510 /// Create a new UserLabel. ----
511 UserLabel(const DILabel *label, DebugLoc L, SlotIndex Idx) 0
512 : Label(label), dl(std::move(L)), loc(Idx) {} 0
513 ----
514 /// Does this UserLabel match the parameters? ----
515 bool matches(const DILabel *L, const DILocation *IA, 0
516 const SlotIndex Index) const { ----
517 return Label == L && dl->getInlinedAt() == IA && loc == Index; 0
518 } ----
519 ----

525 const DebugLoc &getDebugLoc() { return dl; } 0
526 ----
527 void print(raw_ostream &, const TargetRegisterInfo *); ----
528 }; ----

538 /// Position and VReg of a PHI instruction during register allocation. ----
539 struct PHIValPos { ----
540 SlotIndex SI; /// Slot where this PHI occurs. ----
541 Register Reg; /// VReg this PHI occurs in. ----
542 unsigned SubReg; /// Qualifiying subregister for Reg. ----
543 }; ----
544 ----
545 /// Map from debug instruction number to PHI position during allocation. ----
546 std::map PHIValToPos; ----
547 /// Index of, for each VReg, which debug instruction numbers and corresponding ----
548 /// PHIs are sensitive to splitting. Each VReg may have multiple PHI defs, ----
549 /// at different positions. ----
550 DenseMap> RegToPHIIdx; ----
551 ----
552 /// Record for any debug instructions unlinked from their blocks during ----
553 /// regalloc. Stores the instr and it's location, so that they can be ----
554 /// re-inserted after regalloc is over. ----
555 struct InstrPos { ----
556 MachineInstr *MI; ///< Debug instruction, unlinked from it's block. ----
557 SlotIndex Idx; ///< Slot position where MI should be re-inserted. ----
558 MachineBasicBlock *MBB; ///< Block that MI was in. ----
559 }; ----

592 /// Add DBG_VALUE instruction to our maps. ----
593 /// ----

595 /// \param Idx Last valid SLotIndex before instruction. ----

599 ----
600 /// Track variable location debug instructions while using the instruction ----
601 /// referencing implementation. Such debug instructions do not need to be ----
602 /// updated during regalloc because they identify instructions rather than ----
603 /// register locations. However, they needs to be removed from the ----
604 /// MachineFunction during regalloc, then re-inserted later, to avoid ----
605 /// disrupting the allocator. ----

619 bool handleDebugLabel(MachineInstr &MI, SlotIndex Idx); ----

622 /// for each instruction. ----
623 /// ----

629 bool collectDebugValues(MachineFunction &mf, bool InstrRef); ----

719 } ----

773 std::optional Fragment, ----
774 const DebugLoc &DL) { ----
775 // FIXME: Handle partially overlapping fragments. See ----
776 // https://reviews.llvm.org/D70121#1849741. ----
777 DebugVariable ID(Var, Fragment, DL->getInlinedAt()); 0
778 UserValue *&UV = userVarMap[ID]; 0
779 if (!UV) { 0
780 userValues.push_back( 0

782 UV = userValues.back().get(); 0
783 } ----
784 return UV; 0

788 assert(VirtReg.isVirtual() && "Only map VirtRegs"); 0

790 Leader = UserValue::merge(Leader, EC); 0
791 } 0

798 ----
799 bool LDVImpl::handleDebugValue(MachineInstr &MI, SlotIndex Idx) { 0
800 // DBG_VALUE loc, offset, variable, expr ----
801 // DBG_VALUE_LIST variable, expr, locs... ----
802 if (!MI.isDebugValue()) { 0
803 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Can't handle non-DBG_VALUE*: " << MI); 0
804 return false; 0
805 } ----
806 if (!MI.getDebugVariableOp().isMetadata()) { 0
807 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Can't handle DBG_VALUE* with invalid variable: " 0
808 << MI); ----
809 return false; 0
810 } ----
811 if (MI.isNonListDebugValue() && 0
812 (MI.getNumOperands() != 4 || 0
813 !(MI.getDebugOffset().isImm() || MI.getDebugOffset().isReg()))) { 0
814 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Can't handle malformed DBG_VALUE: " << MI); 0
815 return false; 0
816 } ----
817 ----
818 // Detect invalid DBG_VALUE instructions, with a debug-use of a virtual ----
819 // register that hasn't been defined yet. If we do not remove those here, then ----
820 // the re-insertion of the DBG_VALUE instruction after register allocation ----
821 // will be incorrect. ----
822 bool Discard = false; 0
823 for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI.debug_operands()) { 0
824 if (Op.isReg() && Op.getReg().isVirtual()) { 0
825 const Register Reg = Op.getReg(); 0
826 if (!LIS->hasInterval(Reg)) { 0
827 // The DBG_VALUE is described by a virtual register that does not have a ----
828 // live interval. Discard the DBG_VALUE. ----
829 Discard = true; 0
830 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Discarding debug info (no LIS interval): " << Idx 0
831 << " " << MI); ----
832 } else { ----
833 // The DBG_VALUE is only valid if either Reg is live out from Idx, or ----
834 // Reg is defined dead at Idx (where Idx is the slot index for the ----
835 // instruction preceding the DBG_VALUE). ----
836 const LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(Reg); 0
837 LiveQueryResult LRQ = LI.Query(Idx); 0
838 if (!LRQ.valueOutOrDead()) { 0
839 // We have found a DBG_VALUE with the value in a virtual register that ----
840 // is not live. Discard the DBG_VALUE. ----
841 Discard = true; 0
842 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Discarding debug info (reg not live): " << Idx 0
843 << " " << MI); ----
844 } ----
845 } ----
846 } ----
847 } ----
848 ----
849 // Get or create the UserValue for (variable,offset) here. ----
850 bool IsIndirect = MI.isDebugOffsetImm(); 0
851 if (IsIndirect) 0
852 assert(MI.getDebugOffset().getImm() == 0 && 0
853 "DBG_VALUE with nonzero offset"); ----
854 bool IsList = MI.isDebugValueList(); 0
855 const DILocalVariable *Var = MI.getDebugVariable(); 0
856 const DIExpression *Expr = MI.getDebugExpression(); 0
857 UserValue *UV = getUserValue(Var, Expr->getFragmentInfo(), MI.getDebugLoc()); 0
858 if (!Discard) 0
859 UV->addDef(Idx, 0
860 ArrayRef(MI.debug_operands().begin(), 0
861 MI.debug_operands().end()), 0
862 IsIndirect, IsList, *Expr); ----
863 else { ----
864 MachineOperand MO = MachineOperand::CreateReg(0U, false); 0
865 MO.setIsDebug(); 0
866 // We should still pass a list the same size as MI.debug_operands() even if ----
867 // all MOs are undef, so that DbgVariableValue can correctly adjust the ----
868 // expression while removing the duplicated undefs. ----
869 SmallVector UndefMOs(MI.getNumDebugOperands(), MO); 0
870 UV->addDef(Idx, UndefMOs, false, IsList, *Expr); 0
871 } 0
872 return true; 0
873 } ----
874 ----
875 MachineBasicBlock::iterator LDVImpl::handleDebugInstr(MachineInstr &MI, 0
876 SlotIndex Idx) { ----
877 assert(MI.isDebugValueLike() || MI.isDebugPHI()); 0
878 ----
879 // In instruction referencing mode, there should be no DBG_VALUE instructions ----
880 // that refer to virtual registers. They might still refer to constants. ----
881 if (MI.isDebugValueLike()) 0
882 assert(none_of(MI.debug_operands(), 0
883 [](const MachineOperand &MO) { ----
884 return MO.isReg() && MO.getReg().isVirtual(); ----
885 }) && ----
886 "MIs should not refer to Virtual Registers in InstrRef mode."); ----
887 ----
888 // Unlink the instruction, store it in the debug instructions collection. ----
889 auto NextInst = std::next(MI.getIterator()); 0
890 auto *MBB = MI.getParent(); 0
891 MI.removeFromParent(); 0
892 StashedDebugInstrs.push_back({&MI, Idx, MBB}); 0
893 return NextInst; 0
894 } ----
895 ----
896 bool LDVImpl::handleDebugLabel(MachineInstr &MI, SlotIndex Idx) { 0
897 // DBG_LABEL label ----
898 if (MI.getNumOperands() != 1 || !MI.getOperand(0).isMetadata()) { 0
899 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Can't handle " << MI); 0
900 return false; 0
901 } ----
902 ----
903 // Get or create the UserLabel for label here. ----
904 const DILabel *Label = MI.getDebugLabel(); 0
905 const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
906 bool Found = false; 0
907 for (auto const &L : userLabels) { 0
908 if (L->matches(Label, DL->getInlinedAt(), Idx)) { 0
909 Found = true; 0
910 break; 0
911 } ----
912 } ----
913 if (!Found) 0
914 userLabels.push_back(std::make_unique(Label, DL, Idx)); 0
915 ----
916 return true; 0
917 } ----
918 ----
919 bool LDVImpl::collectDebugValues(MachineFunction &mf, bool InstrRef) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
920 bool Changed = false; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
921 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : mf) { 5 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
922 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MBB.begin(), MBBE = MBB.end(); 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
923 MBBI != MBBE;) { 22 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
924 // Use the first debug instruction in the sequence to get a SlotIndex ----
925 // for following consecutive debug instructions. ----
926 if (!MBBI->isDebugOrPseudoInstr()) { 18 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
927 ++MBBI; 18 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
928 continue; 18 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
929 } ----
930 // Debug instructions has no slot index. Use the previous ----
931 // non-debug instruction's SlotIndex as its SlotIndex. ----
932 SlotIndex Idx = ----
933 MBBI == MBB.begin() 0
934 ? LIS->getMBBStartIdx(&MBB) 0
935 : LIS->getInstructionIndex(*std::prev(MBBI)).getRegSlot(); 0
936 // Handle consecutive debug instructions with the same slot index. ----
937 do { ----
938 // In instruction referencing mode, pass each instr to handleDebugInstr ----
939 // to be unlinked. Ignore DBG_VALUE_LISTs -- they refer to vregs, and ----
940 // need to go through the normal live interval splitting process. ----
941 if (InstrRef && (MBBI->isNonListDebugValue() || MBBI->isDebugPHI() || 0
942 MBBI->isDebugRef())) { 0
943 MBBI = handleDebugInstr(*MBBI, Idx); 0
944 Changed = true; 0
945 // In normal debug mode, use the dedicated DBG_VALUE / DBG_LABEL handler ----
946 // to track things through register allocation, and erase the instr. ----
947 } else if ((MBBI->isDebugValue() && handleDebugValue(*MBBI, Idx)) || 0
948 (MBBI->isDebugLabel() && handleDebugLabel(*MBBI, Idx))) { 0
949 MBBI = MBB.erase(MBBI); 0
950 Changed = true; 0
951 } else ----
952 ++MBBI; 0
953 } while (MBBI != MBBE && MBBI->isDebugOrPseudoInstr()); 0
954 } ----
955 } ----
956 return Changed; 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
957 } ----
958 ----
959 void UserValue::extendDef( 0
960 SlotIndex Idx, DbgVariableValue DbgValue, ----
961 SmallDenseMap> ----
962 &LiveIntervalInfo, ----
963 std::optional>> &Kills, ----
964 LiveIntervals &LIS) { ----
965 SlotIndex Start = Idx; 0
966 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = LIS.getMBBFromIndex(Start); 0
967 SlotIndex Stop = LIS.getMBBEndIdx(MBB); 0
968 LocMap::iterator I = locInts.find(Start); 0
969 ----
970 // Limit to the intersection of the VNIs' live ranges. ----
971 for (auto &LII : LiveIntervalInfo) { 0
972 LiveRange *LR = LII.second.first; 0
973 assert(LR && LII.second.second && "Missing range info for Idx."); 0
974 LiveInterval::Segment *Segment = LR->getSegmentContaining(Start); 0
975 assert(Segment && Segment->valno == LII.second.second && 0
976 "Invalid VNInfo for Idx given?"); ----
977 if (Segment->end < Stop) { 0
978 Stop = Segment->end; 0
979 Kills = {Stop, {LII.first}}; 0
980 } else if (Segment->end == Stop && Kills) { 0
981 // If multiple locations end at the same place, track all of them in ----
982 // Kills. ----
983 Kills->second.push_back(LII.first); 0
984 } ----
985 } ----
986 ----
987 // There could already be a short def at Start. ----
988 if (I.valid() && I.start() <= Start) { 0
989 // Stop when meeting a different location or an already extended interval. ----
990 Start = Start.getNextSlot(); 0
991 if (I.value() != DbgValue || I.stop() != Start) { 0
992 // Clear `Kills`, as we have a new def available. ----
993 Kills = std::nullopt; 0
994 return; 0
995 } ----
996 // This is a one-slot placeholder. Just skip it. ----
997 ++I; 0
998 } ----
999 ----
1000 // Limited by the next def. ----
1001 if (I.valid() && I.start() < Stop) { 0
1002 Stop = I.start(); 0
1003 // Clear `Kills`, as we have a new def available. ----
1004 Kills = std::nullopt; 0
1005 } ----
1006 ----
1007 if (Start < Stop) { 0
1008 DbgVariableValue ExtDbgValue(DbgValue); 0
1009 I.insert(Start, Stop, std::move(ExtDbgValue)); 0
1010 } 0
1011 } 0
1012 ----
1013 void UserValue::addDefsFromCopies( 0
1014 DbgVariableValue DbgValue, ----
1015 SmallVectorImpl> &LocIntervals, ----
1016 SlotIndex KilledAt, ----
1017 SmallVectorImpl> &NewDefs, ----
1018 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI, LiveIntervals &LIS) { ----
1019 // Don't track copies from physregs, there are too many uses. ----
1020 if (any_of(LocIntervals, 0
1021 [](auto LocI) { return !LocI.second->reg().isVirtual(); })) 0
1022 return; 0
1023 ----
1024 // Collect all the (vreg, valno) pairs that are copies of LI. ----
1025 SmallDenseMap ----
1026 SmallVector, 4>> ----
1027 CopyValues; 0
1028 for (auto &LocInterval : LocIntervals) { 0
1029 unsigned LocNo = LocInterval.first; 0
1030 LiveInterval *LI = LocInterval.second; 0
1031 for (MachineOperand &MO : MRI.use_nodbg_operands(LI->reg())) { 0
1032 MachineInstr *MI = MO.getParent(); 0
1033 // Copies of the full value. ----
1034 if (MO.getSubReg() || !MI->isCopy()) 0
1035 continue; 0
1036 Register DstReg = MI->getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1037 ----
1038 // Don't follow copies to physregs. These are usually setting up call ----
1039 // arguments, and the argument registers are always call clobbered. We are ----
1040 // better off in the source register which could be a callee-saved ----
1041 // register, or it could be spilled. ----
1042 if (!DstReg.isVirtual()) 0
1043 continue; 0
1044 ----
1045 // Is the value extended to reach this copy? If not, another def may be ----
1046 // blocking it, or we are looking at a wrong value of LI. ----
1047 SlotIndex Idx = LIS.getInstructionIndex(*MI); 0
1048 LocMap::iterator I = locInts.find(Idx.getRegSlot(true)); 0
1049 if (!I.valid() || I.value() != DbgValue) 0
1050 continue; 0
1051 ----
1052 if (!LIS.hasInterval(DstReg)) 0
1053 continue; 0
1054 LiveInterval *DstLI = &LIS.getInterval(DstReg); 0
1055 const VNInfo *DstVNI = DstLI->getVNInfoAt(Idx.getRegSlot()); 0
1056 assert(DstVNI && DstVNI->def == Idx.getRegSlot() && "Bad copy value"); 0
1057 CopyValues[LocNo].push_back(std::make_pair(DstLI, DstVNI)); 0
1058 } 0
1059 } ----
1060 ----
1061 if (CopyValues.empty()) 0
1062 return; 0
1063 ----
1064 #if !defined(NDEBUG) ----
1065 for (auto &LocInterval : LocIntervals) 0
1066 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Got " << CopyValues[LocInterval.first].size() 0
1067 << " copies of " << *LocInterval.second << '\n'); ----
1068 #endif ----
1069 ----
1070 // Try to add defs of the copied values for the kill point. Check that there ----
1071 // isn't already a def at Idx. ----
1072 LocMap::iterator I = locInts.find(KilledAt); 0
1073 if (I.valid() && I.start() <= KilledAt) 0
1074 return; 0
1075 DbgVariableValue NewValue(DbgValue); 0
1076 for (auto &LocInterval : LocIntervals) { 0
1077 unsigned LocNo = LocInterval.first; 0
1078 bool FoundCopy = false; 0
1079 for (auto &LIAndVNI : CopyValues[LocNo]) { 0
1080 LiveInterval *DstLI = LIAndVNI.first; 0
1081 const VNInfo *DstVNI = LIAndVNI.second; 0
1082 if (DstLI->getVNInfoAt(KilledAt) != DstVNI) 0
1083 continue; 0
1084 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Kill at " << KilledAt << " covered by valno #" 0
1085 << DstVNI->id << " in " << *DstLI << '\n'); ----
1086 MachineInstr *CopyMI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(DstVNI->def); 0
1087 assert(CopyMI && CopyMI->isCopy() && "Bad copy value"); 0
1088 unsigned NewLocNo = getLocationNo(CopyMI->getOperand(0)); 0
1089 NewValue = NewValue.changeLocNo(LocNo, NewLocNo); 0
1090 FoundCopy = true; 0
1091 break; 0
1092 } ----
1093 // If there are any killed locations we can't find a copy for, we can't ----
1094 // extend the variable value. ----
1095 if (!FoundCopy) 0
1096 return; 0
1097 } ----
1098 I.insert(KilledAt, KilledAt.getNextSlot(), NewValue); 0
1099 NewDefs.push_back(std::make_pair(KilledAt, NewValue)); 0
1100 } 0
1101 ----
1102 void UserValue::computeIntervals(MachineRegisterInfo &MRI, 0
1103 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, ----
1104 LiveIntervals &LIS, LexicalScopes &LS) { ----
1105 SmallVector, 16> Defs; 0
1106 ----
1107 // Collect all defs to be extended (Skipping undefs). ----
1108 for (LocMap::const_iterator I = locInts.begin(); I.valid(); ++I) 0
1109 if (!I.value().isUndef()) 0
1110 Defs.push_back(std::make_pair(I.start(), I.value())); 0
1111 ----
1112 // Extend all defs, and possibly add new ones along the way. ----
1113 for (unsigned i = 0; i != Defs.size(); ++i) { 0
1114 SlotIndex Idx = Defs[i].first; 0
1115 DbgVariableValue DbgValue = Defs[i].second; 0
1116 SmallDenseMap> LIs; 0
1117 SmallVector VNIs; 0
1118 bool ShouldExtendDef = false; 0
1119 for (unsigned LocNo : DbgValue.loc_nos()) { 0
1120 const MachineOperand &LocMO = locations[LocNo]; 0
1121 if (!LocMO.isReg() || !LocMO.getReg().isVirtual()) { 0
1122 ShouldExtendDef |= !LocMO.isReg(); 0
1123 continue; 0
1124 } ----
1125 ShouldExtendDef = true; 0
1126 LiveInterval *LI = nullptr; 0
1127 const VNInfo *VNI = nullptr; 0
1128 if (LIS.hasInterval(LocMO.getReg())) { 0
1129 LI = &LIS.getInterval(LocMO.getReg()); 0
1130 VNI = LI->getVNInfoAt(Idx); 0
1131 } ----
1132 if (LI && VNI) 0
1133 LIs[LocNo] = {LI, VNI}; 0
1134 } ----
1135 if (ShouldExtendDef) { 0
1136 std::optional>> Kills; 0
1137 extendDef(Idx, DbgValue, LIs, Kills, LIS); 0
1138 ----
1139 if (Kills) { 0
1140 SmallVector, 2> KilledLocIntervals; 0
1141 bool AnySubreg = false; 0
1142 for (unsigned LocNo : Kills->second) { 0
1143 const MachineOperand &LocMO = this->locations[LocNo]; 0
1144 if (LocMO.getSubReg()) { 0
1145 AnySubreg = true; 0
1146 break; 0
1147 } ----
1148 LiveInterval *LI = &LIS.getInterval(LocMO.getReg()); 0
1149 KilledLocIntervals.push_back({LocNo, LI}); 0
1150 } ----
1151 ----
1152 // FIXME: Handle sub-registers in addDefsFromCopies. The problem is that ----
1153 // if the original location for example is %vreg0:sub_hi, and we find a ----
1154 // full register copy in addDefsFromCopies (at the moment it only ----
1155 // handles full register copies), then we must add the sub1 sub-register ----
1156 // index to the new location. However, that is only possible if the new ----
1157 // virtual register is of the same regclass (or if there is an ----
1158 // equivalent sub-register in that regclass). For now, simply skip ----
1159 // handling copies if a sub-register is involved. ----
1160 if (!AnySubreg) 0
1161 addDefsFromCopies(DbgValue, KilledLocIntervals, Kills->first, Defs, 0
1162 MRI, LIS); ----
1163 } 0
1164 } 0
1165 ----
1166 // For physregs, we only mark the start slot idx. DwarfDebug will see it ----
1167 // as if the DBG_VALUE is valid up until the end of the basic block, or ----
1168 // the next def of the physical register. So we do not need to extend the ----
1169 // range. It might actually happen that the DBG_VALUE is the last use of ----
1170 // the physical register (e.g. if this is an unused input argument to a ----
1171 // function). ----
1172 } 0
1173 ----
1174 // The computed intervals may extend beyond the range of the debug ----
1175 // location's lexical scope. In this case, splitting of an interval ----
1176 // can result in an interval outside of the scope being created, ----
1177 // causing extra unnecessary DBG_VALUEs to be emitted. To prevent ----
1178 // this, trim the intervals to the lexical scope in the case of inlined ----
1179 // variables, since heavy inlining may cause production of dramatically big ----
1180 // number of DBG_VALUEs to be generated. ----
1181 if (!dl.getInlinedAt()) 0
1182 return; 0
1183 ----
1184 LexicalScope *Scope = LS.findLexicalScope(dl); 0
1185 if (!Scope) 0
1186 return; 0
1187 ----
1188 SlotIndex PrevEnd; 0
1189 LocMap::iterator I = locInts.begin(); 0
1190 ----
1191 // Iterate over the lexical scope ranges. Each time round the loop ----
1192 // we check the intervals for overlap with the end of the previous ----
1193 // range and the start of the next. The first range is handled as ----
1194 // a special case where there is no PrevEnd. ----
1195 for (const InsnRange &Range : Scope->getRanges()) { 0
1196 SlotIndex RStart = LIS.getInstructionIndex(*Range.first); 0
1197 SlotIndex REnd = LIS.getInstructionIndex(*Range.second); 0
1198 ----
1199 // Variable locations at the first instruction of a block should be ----
1200 // based on the block's SlotIndex, not the first instruction's index. ----
1201 if (Range.first == Range.first->getParent()->begin()) 0
1202 RStart = LIS.getSlotIndexes()->getIndexBefore(*Range.first); 0
1203 ----
1204 // At the start of each iteration I has been advanced so that ----
1205 // I.stop() >= PrevEnd. Check for overlap. ----
1206 if (PrevEnd && I.start() < PrevEnd) { 0
1207 SlotIndex IStop = I.stop(); 0
1208 DbgVariableValue DbgValue = I.value(); 0
1209 ----
1210 // Stop overlaps previous end - trim the end of the interval to ----
1211 // the scope range. ----
1212 I.setStopUnchecked(PrevEnd); 0
1213 ++I; 0
1214 ----
1215 // If the interval also overlaps the start of the "next" (i.e. ----
1216 // current) range create a new interval for the remainder (which ----
1217 // may be further trimmed). ----
1218 if (RStart < IStop) 0
1219 I.insert(RStart, IStop, DbgValue); 0
1220 } 0
1221 ----
1222 // Advance I so that I.stop() >= RStart, and check for overlap. ----
1223 I.advanceTo(RStart); 0
1224 if (!I.valid()) 0
1225 return; 0
1226 ----
1227 if (I.start() < RStart) { 0
1228 // Interval start overlaps range - trim to the scope range. ----
1229 I.setStartUnchecked(RStart); 0
1230 // Remember that this interval was trimmed. ----
1231 trimmedDefs.insert(RStart); 0
1232 } ----
1233 ----
1234 // The end of a lexical scope range is the last instruction in the ----
1235 // range. To convert to an interval we need the index of the ----
1236 // instruction after it. ----
1237 REnd = REnd.getNextIndex(); 0
1238 ----
1239 // Advance I to first interval outside current range. ----
1240 I.advanceTo(REnd); 0
1241 if (!I.valid()) 0
1242 return; 0
1243 ----
1244 PrevEnd = REnd; 0
1245 } ----
1246 ----
1247 // Check for overlap with end of final range. ----
1248 if (PrevEnd && I.start() < PrevEnd) 0
1249 I.setStopUnchecked(PrevEnd); 0
1250 } 0

1254 LS.initialize(*MF); 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1255 ----
1256 for (unsigned i = 0, e = userValues.size(); i != e; ++i) { 1 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll
1257 userValues[i]->computeIntervals(MF->getRegInfo(), *TRI, *LIS, LS); 0

1330 ----
1331 bool ----
1332 UserValue::splitLocation(unsigned OldLocNo, ArrayRef NewRegs, 0
1333 LiveIntervals& LIS) { ----
1334 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1335 dbgs() << "Splitting Loc" << OldLocNo << '\t'; ----
1336 print(dbgs(), nullptr); ----
1337 }); ----
1338 bool DidChange = false; 0
1339 LocMap::iterator LocMapI; 0
1340 LocMapI.setMap(locInts); 0
1341 for (Register NewReg : NewRegs) { 0
1342 LiveInterval *LI = &LIS.getInterval(NewReg); 0
1343 if (LI->empty()) 0
1344 continue; 0
1345 ----
1346 // Don't allocate the new LocNo until it is needed. ----
1347 unsigned NewLocNo = UndefLocNo; 0
1348 ----
1349 // Iterate over the overlaps between locInts and LI. ----
1350 LocMapI.find(LI->beginIndex()); 0
1351 if (!LocMapI.valid()) 0
1352 continue; 0
1353 LiveInterval::iterator LII = LI->advanceTo(LI->begin(), LocMapI.start()); 0
1354 LiveInterval::iterator LIE = LI->end(); 0
1355 while (LocMapI.valid() && LII != LIE) { 0
1356 // At this point, we know that LocMapI.stop() > LII->start. ----
1357 LII = LI->advanceTo(LII, LocMapI.start()); 0
1358 if (LII == LIE) 0
1359 break; 0
1360 ----
1361 // Now LII->end > LocMapI.start(). Do we have an overlap? ----
1362 if (LocMapI.value().containsLocNo(OldLocNo) && 0
1363 LII->start < LocMapI.stop()) { 0
1364 // Overlapping correct location. Allocate NewLocNo now. ----
1365 if (NewLocNo == UndefLocNo) { 0
1366 MachineOperand MO = MachineOperand::CreateReg(LI->reg(), false); 0
1367 MO.setSubReg(locations[OldLocNo].getSubReg()); 0
1368 NewLocNo = getLocationNo(MO); 0
1369 DidChange = true; 0
1370 } ----
1371 ----
1372 SlotIndex LStart = LocMapI.start(); 0
1373 SlotIndex LStop = LocMapI.stop(); 0
1374 DbgVariableValue OldDbgValue = LocMapI.value(); 0
1375 ----
1376 // Trim LocMapI down to the LII overlap. ----
1377 if (LStart < LII->start) 0
1378 LocMapI.setStartUnchecked(LII->start); 0
1379 if (LStop > LII->end) 0
1380 LocMapI.setStopUnchecked(LII->end); 0
1381 ----
1382 // Change the value in the overlap. This may trigger coalescing. ----
1383 LocMapI.setValue(OldDbgValue.changeLocNo(OldLocNo, NewLocNo)); 0
1384 ----
1385 // Re-insert any removed OldDbgValue ranges. ----
1386 if (LStart < LocMapI.start()) { 0
1387 LocMapI.insert(LStart, LocMapI.start(), OldDbgValue); 0
1388 ++LocMapI; 0
1389 assert(LocMapI.valid() && "Unexpected coalescing"); 0
1390 } ----
1391 if (LStop > LocMapI.stop()) { 0
1392 ++LocMapI; 0
1393 LocMapI.insert(LII->end, LStop, OldDbgValue); 0
1394 --LocMapI; 0
1395 } ----
1396 } 0
1397 ----
1398 // Advance to the next overlap. ----
1399 if (LII->end < LocMapI.stop()) { 0
1400 if (++LII == LIE) 0
1401 break; 0
1402 LocMapI.advanceTo(LII->start); 0
1403 } else { ----
1404 ++LocMapI; 0
1405 if (!LocMapI.valid()) 0
1406 break; 0
1407 LII = LI->advanceTo(LII, LocMapI.start()); 0
1408 } ----
1409 } ----
1410 } ----
1411 ----
1412 // Finally, remove OldLocNo unless it is still used by some interval in the ----
1413 // locInts map. One case when OldLocNo still is in use is when the register ----
1414 // has been spilled. In such situations the spilled register is kept as a ----
1415 // location until rewriteLocations is called (VirtRegMap is mapping the old ----
1416 // register to the spill slot). So for a while we can have locations that map ----
1417 // to virtual registers that have been removed from both the MachineFunction ----
1418 // and from LiveIntervals. ----
1419 // ----
1420 // We may also just be using the location for a value with a different ----
1421 // expression. ----
1422 removeLocationIfUnused(OldLocNo); 0
1423 ----
1424 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1425 dbgs() << "Split result: \t"; ----
1426 print(dbgs(), nullptr); ----
1427 }); ----
1428 return DidChange; 0
1429 } 0
1430 ----
1431 bool ----
1432 UserValue::splitRegister(Register OldReg, ArrayRef NewRegs, 0
1433 LiveIntervals &LIS) { ----
1434 bool DidChange = false; 0
1435 // Split locations referring to OldReg. Iterate backwards so splitLocation can ----
1436 // safely erase unused locations. ----
1437 for (unsigned i = locations.size(); i ; --i) { 0
1438 unsigned LocNo = i-1; 0
1439 const MachineOperand *Loc = &locations[LocNo]; 0
1440 if (!Loc->isReg() || Loc->getReg() != OldReg) 0
1441 continue; 0
1442 DidChange |= splitLocation(LocNo, NewRegs, LIS); 0
1443 } ----
1444 return DidChange; 0
1445 } ----
1446 ----
1447 void LDVImpl::splitPHIRegister(Register OldReg, ArrayRef NewRegs) { 0
1448 auto RegIt = RegToPHIIdx.find(OldReg); 0
1449 if (RegIt == RegToPHIIdx.end()) 0
1450 return; 0
1451 ----
1452 std::vector> NewRegIdxes; 0
1453 // Iterate over all the debug instruction numbers affected by this split. ----
1454 for (unsigned InstrID : RegIt->second) { 0
1455 auto PHIIt = PHIValToPos.find(InstrID); 0
1456 assert(PHIIt != PHIValToPos.end()); 0
1457 const SlotIndex &Slot = PHIIt->second.SI; 0
1458 assert(OldReg == PHIIt->second.Reg); 0
1459 ----
1460 // Find the new register that covers this position. ----
1461 for (auto NewReg : NewRegs) { 0
1462 const LiveInterval &LI = LIS->getInterval(NewReg); 0
1463 auto LII = LI.find(Slot); 0
1464 if (LII != LI.end() && LII->start <= Slot) { 0
1465 // This new register covers this PHI position, record this for indexing. ----
1466 NewRegIdxes.push_back(std::make_pair(NewReg, InstrID)); 0
1467 // Record that this value lives in a different VReg now. ----
1468 PHIIt->second.Reg = NewReg; 0
1469 break; 0
1470 } ----
1471 } ----
1472 ----
1473 // If we do not find a new register covering this PHI, then register ----
1474 // allocation has dropped its location, for example because it's not live. ----
1475 // The old VReg will not be mapped to a physreg, and the instruction ----
1476 // number will have been optimized out. ----
1477 } ----
1478 ----
1479 // Re-create register index using the new register numbers. ----
1480 RegToPHIIdx.erase(RegIt); 0
1481 for (auto &RegAndInstr : NewRegIdxes) 0
1482 RegToPHIIdx[RegAndInstr.first].push_back(RegAndInstr.second); 0
1483 } 0
1484 ----
1485 void LDVImpl::splitRegister(Register OldReg, ArrayRef NewRegs) { 0
1486 // Consider whether this split range affects any PHI locations. ----
1487 splitPHIRegister(OldReg, NewRegs); 0
1488 ----
1489 // Check whether any intervals mapped by a DBG_VALUE were split and need ----
1490 // updating. ----
1491 bool DidChange = false; 0
1492 for (UserValue *UV = lookupVirtReg(OldReg); UV; UV = UV->getNext()) 0
1493 DidChange |= UV->splitRegister(OldReg, NewRegs, *LIS); 0
1494 ----
1495 if (!DidChange) 0
1496 return; 0
1497 ----
1498 // Map all of the new virtual registers. ----
1499 UserValue *UV = lookupVirtReg(OldReg); 0
1500 for (Register NewReg : NewRegs) 0
1501 mapVirtReg(NewReg, UV); 0
1502 } ----
1503 ----
1504 void LiveDebugVariables:: 0
1505 splitRegister(Register OldReg, ArrayRef NewRegs, LiveIntervals &LIS) { ----
1506 if (pImpl) 0
1507 static_cast(pImpl)->splitRegister(OldReg, NewRegs); 0
1508 } 0
1509 ----
1510 void UserValue::rewriteLocations(VirtRegMap &VRM, const MachineFunction &MF, 0
1511 const TargetInstrInfo &TII, ----
1512 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, ----
1513 SpillOffsetMap &SpillOffsets) { ----
1514 // Build a set of new locations with new numbers so we can coalesce our ----
1515 // IntervalMap if two vreg intervals collapse to the same physical location. ----
1516 // Use MapVector instead of SetVector because MapVector::insert returns the ----
1517 // position of the previously or newly inserted element. The boolean value ----
1518 // tracks if the location was produced by a spill. ----
1519 // FIXME: This will be problematic if we ever support direct and indirect ----
1520 // frame index locations, i.e. expressing both variables in memory and ----
1521 // 'int x, *px = &x'. The "spilled" bit must become part of the location. ----
1522 MapVector> NewLocations; 0
1523 SmallVector LocNoMap(locations.size()); 0
1524 for (unsigned I = 0, E = locations.size(); I != E; ++I) { 0
1525 bool Spilled = false; 0
1526 unsigned SpillOffset = 0; 0
1527 MachineOperand Loc = locations[I]; 0
1528 // Only virtual registers are rewritten. ----
1529 if (Loc.isReg() && Loc.getReg() && Loc.getReg().isVirtual()) { 0
1530 Register VirtReg = Loc.getReg(); 0
1531 if (VRM.isAssignedReg(VirtReg) && 0
1532 Register::isPhysicalRegister(VRM.getPhys(VirtReg))) { 0
1533 // This can create a %noreg operand in rare cases when the sub-register ----
1534 // index is no longer available. That means the user value is in a ----
1535 // non-existent sub-register, and %noreg is exactly what we want. ----
1536 Loc.substPhysReg(VRM.getPhys(VirtReg), TRI); 0
1537 } else if (VRM.getStackSlot(VirtReg) != VirtRegMap::NO_STACK_SLOT) { 0
1538 // Retrieve the stack slot offset. ----
1539 unsigned SpillSize; ----
1540 const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo(); 0
1541 const TargetRegisterClass *TRC = MRI.getRegClass(VirtReg); 0
1542 bool Success = TII.getStackSlotRange(TRC, Loc.getSubReg(), SpillSize, 0
1543 SpillOffset, MF); ----
1544 ----
1545 // FIXME: Invalidate the location if the offset couldn't be calculated. ----
1546 (void)Success; ----
1547 ----
1548 Loc = MachineOperand::CreateFI(VRM.getStackSlot(VirtReg)); 0
1549 Spilled = true; 0
1550 } else { ----
1551 Loc.setReg(0); 0
1552 Loc.setSubReg(0); 0
1553 } ----
1554 } ----
1555 ----
1556 // Insert this location if it doesn't already exist and record a mapping ----
1557 // from the old number to the new number. ----
1558 auto InsertResult = NewLocations.insert({Loc, {Spilled, SpillOffset}}); 0
1559 unsigned NewLocNo = std::distance(NewLocations.begin(), InsertResult.first); 0
1560 LocNoMap[I] = NewLocNo; 0
1561 } ----
1562 ----
1563 // Rewrite the locations and record the stack slot offsets for spills. ----
1564 locations.clear(); 0
1565 SpillOffsets.clear(); 0
1566 for (auto &Pair : NewLocations) { 0
1567 bool Spilled; ----
1568 unsigned SpillOffset; ----
1569 std::tie(Spilled, SpillOffset) = Pair.second; 0
1570 locations.push_back(Pair.first); 0
1571 if (Spilled) { 0
1572 unsigned NewLocNo = std::distance(&*NewLocations.begin(), &Pair); 0
1573 SpillOffsets[NewLocNo] = SpillOffset; 0
1574 } ----
1575 } ----
1576 ----
1577 // Update the interval map, but only coalesce left, since intervals to the ----
1578 // right use the old location numbers. This should merge two contiguous ----
1579 // DBG_VALUE intervals with different vregs that were allocated to the same ----
1580 // physical register. ----
1581 for (LocMap::iterator I = locInts.begin(); I.valid(); ++I) { 0
1582 I.setValueUnchecked(I.value().remapLocNos(LocNoMap)); 0
1583 I.setStart(I.start()); 0
1584 } 0
1585 } 0
1586 ----
1587 /// Find an iterator for inserting a DBG_VALUE instruction. ----
1588 static MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
1589 findInsertLocation(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, SlotIndex Idx, LiveIntervals &LIS, 0
1590 BlockSkipInstsMap &BBSkipInstsMap) { ----
1591 SlotIndex Start = LIS.getMBBStartIdx(MBB); 0
1592 Idx = Idx.getBaseIndex(); 0
1593 ----
1594 // Try to find an insert location by going backwards from Idx. ----
1595 MachineInstr *MI; ----
1596 while (!(MI = LIS.getInstructionFromIndex(Idx))) { 0
1597 // We've reached the beginning of MBB. ----
1598 if (Idx == Start) { 0
1599 // Retrieve the last PHI/Label/Debug location found when calling ----
1600 // SkipPHIsLabelsAndDebug last time. Start searching from there. ----
1601 // ----
1602 // Note the iterator kept in BBSkipInstsMap is one step back based ----
1603 // on the iterator returned by SkipPHIsLabelsAndDebug last time. ----
1604 // One exception is when SkipPHIsLabelsAndDebug returns MBB->begin(), ----
1605 // BBSkipInstsMap won't save it. This is to consider the case that ----
1606 // new instructions may be inserted at the beginning of MBB after ----
1607 // last call of SkipPHIsLabelsAndDebug. If we save MBB->begin() in ----
1608 // BBSkipInstsMap, after new non-phi/non-label/non-debug instructions ----
1609 // are inserted at the beginning of the MBB, the iterator in ----
1610 // BBSkipInstsMap won't point to the beginning of the MBB anymore. ----
1611 // Therefore The next search in SkipPHIsLabelsAndDebug will skip those ----
1612 // newly added instructions and that is unwanted. ----
1613 MachineBasicBlock::iterator BeginIt; 0
1614 auto MapIt = BBSkipInstsMap.find(MBB); 0
1615 if (MapIt == BBSkipInstsMap.end()) 0
1616 BeginIt = MBB->begin(); 0
1617 else ----
1618 BeginIt = std::next(MapIt->second); 0
1619 auto I = MBB->SkipPHIsLabelsAndDebug(BeginIt); 0
1620 if (I != BeginIt) 0
1621 BBSkipInstsMap[MBB] = std::prev(I); 0
1622 return I; 0
1623 } ----
1624 Idx = Idx.getPrevIndex(); 0
1625 } ----
1626 ----
1627 // Don't insert anything after the first terminator, though. ----
1628 return MI->isTerminator() ? MBB->getFirstTerminator() : 0
1629 std::next(MachineBasicBlock::iterator(MI)); 0
1630 } ----
1631 ----
1632 /// Find an iterator for inserting the next DBG_VALUE instruction ----
1633 /// (or end if no more insert locations found). ----
1634 static MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
1635 findNextInsertLocation(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator I, 0
1636 SlotIndex StopIdx, ArrayRef LocMOs, ----
1637 LiveIntervals &LIS, const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI) { ----
1638 SmallVector Regs; 0
1639 for (const MachineOperand &LocMO : LocMOs) 0
1640 if (LocMO.isReg()) 0
1641 Regs.push_back(LocMO.getReg()); 0
1642 if (Regs.empty()) 0
1643 return MBB->instr_end(); 0
1644 ----
1645 // Find the next instruction in the MBB that define the register Reg. ----
1646 while (I != MBB->end() && !I->isTerminator()) { 0
1647 if (!LIS.isNotInMIMap(*I) && 0
1648 SlotIndex::isEarlierEqualInstr(StopIdx, LIS.getInstructionIndex(*I))) 0
1649 break; 0
1650 if (any_of(Regs, [&I, &TRI](Register &Reg) { 0
1651 return I->definesRegister(Reg, &TRI); 0
1652 })) ----
1653 // The insert location is directly after the instruction/bundle. ----
1654 return std::next(I); 0
1655 ++I; 0
1656 } ----
1657 return MBB->end(); 0
1658 } 0
1659 ----
1660 void UserValue::insertDebugValue(MachineBasicBlock *MBB, SlotIndex StartIdx, 0
1661 SlotIndex StopIdx, DbgVariableValue DbgValue, ----
1662 ArrayRef LocSpills, ----
1663 ArrayRef SpillOffsets, ----
1664 LiveIntervals &LIS, const TargetInstrInfo &TII, ----
1665 const TargetRegisterInfo &TRI, ----
1666 BlockSkipInstsMap &BBSkipInstsMap) { ----
1667 SlotIndex MBBEndIdx = LIS.getMBBEndIdx(&*MBB); 0
1668 // Only search within the current MBB. ----
1669 StopIdx = (MBBEndIdx < StopIdx) ? MBBEndIdx : StopIdx; 0
